{
  "texts": [
    "This integration allows the capture of fine-grained spatial details through CNNs and models the global context and long-range dependencies through transformers.",
    "Additionally, the proposed method addresses the limitations of TransUNet, which is one of the few methods that incorporates both CNNs and transformers, by introducing an efficientNetV2 encoder and a CAF module.",
    "These enhancements improve the understanding of complex spatial relationships, facilitate effective feature combinations, and enhance segmentation and classification accuracy.",
    "Furthermore, the exploration of ViTs and MLP-Mixer models as alternative classification approaches adds novelty, offering insights into the effectiveness of attention mechanisms and MLPs in BUS image classification.",
    "MethodsIn this study, we propose an efficient multi-task framework for segmenting and classifying tumors from BUS images."
  ]
}